main event: A civilian witnessed an unidentified object in the sky over Van Nuys, California on June 24, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5-10 minutes.
There were photographs taken of the object, but they are not included in the report.
The witness reported that the object appeared to be solid, transparent, or vapor-like, and looked like a light that was brighter than the brightest stars.
The object was observed to appear and disappear, and the witness was unable to determine which direction it went when it disappeared.

The witness reported that the object seemed to be sinking below a mountain before the main event occurred, and some people who came later also saw a similar object before sunrise in the same general area.
sighted object: an unidentified object or light in the sky
photographs: yes, but not included in the report
